  "text": "Therefore to understand the various possibe mechanisms underlying wortmannin radiosensitization, we used various cells derived from different species (hamster, mouse, chicken and human) in the present study. Moreover, the use of chicken Blymphocyte DT40 cells and their mutant cells with the distinctive defect in DSB repair pathways, either in HR or NHEJ, facilitated the understanding of wortmannin radiosensitization mediated through DSB repair in these cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
